<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2248] Use Apache Rat to enforce copyright headers</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2248</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Follow up to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2161&quot; title=&quot;Fix a few copyrights&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2161&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2161&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Use Apache Rat during builds to make sure copyright headers are present so we don&apos;t forget any and don&apos;t allow any incorrect ones to be checked in.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
